com.hannesdorfmann.mosby3.mvp.viewstate.lce.data

Class RetainingLceViewState<D,V extends MvpLceView<D>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hannesdorfmann.mosby3.mvp.viewstate.lce.AbsLceViewState<D,V>
      • com.hannesdorfmann.mosby3.mvp.viewstate.lce.data.RetainingLceViewState<D,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - the data / model type
    V - the type of the view
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LceViewState<D,V>, ViewState<V>

    public class RetainingLceViewState<D,V extends MvpLceView<D>>
extends AbsLceViewState<D,V>
    This allows one to store / restore any kind of data along orientation changes. So this ViewState will not be saved into the Bundle of saveInstanceState(). This ViewState will be stored and restored directly by the Activity or Fragment itself.
    Since:
    2.0.0
